HEADWORD: Sound
<hw>Sound</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>sund</ets> a
swimming, akin to E. <ets>swim</ets>. See <er>Swim</er>.]</ety> <def>The
air bladder of a fish; <as>as, cod <ex>sounds</ex> are an esteemed
article of food</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

